<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Further Reaction to Downing of Aircraft Over Bosnia </TI></H3>
<H4>   Ruehe Welcomes Actions </H4>
<F P=102> LD0103164994 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1559 GMT 1 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0103164994 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DDP/ADN) -- German Defense Minister Volker 
Ruehe has welcomed NATO's actions in the Bosnian conflict. 
Ruehe was commenting to the CDU/CSU [Christian Democratic 
Union/Christian Social Union] Bundestag group in Bonn today on 
the shooting down of four Serb aircraft by U.S. fighters over 
Bosnia-Herzegovina. Peace could only be achieved if the 
decisions made by the United Nations were implemented. The Serb 
aircraft had violated the UN no-fly zone. 
  Ruehe described it as "right" that German soldiers had been 
on board the AWACS reconnaisance aircraft during the mission. 
He said he was satisfied that the German Government had decided 
in favor of the participation of German soldiers in the 
reconnaisance flights. 

</TEXT>

