<F P=100> AUSTRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Poll Shows Majority Favor EU Membership </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0303105294 Vienna NEUE KRONEN-ZEITUNG in German 3 Mar 94 p 
5 </F>

<F P=103> AU0303105294 </F>
<F P=104>  Vienna NEUE KRONEN-ZEITUNG </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Peter Gnam: "Majority Says `Yes' to European </F>
Union!"] 
  [Excerpt] Vienna -- After the agreement in Brussels, the 
Austrians seem to have been seized with euphoria for Europe: A 
poll that was exclusively carried out by the OGM [Austrian 
Marketing Company] on behalf of NEUE KRONEN-ZEITUNG shows that 
the majority now says `yes' to entry into the European Union 
[EU]. However, this only shows the mood at the moment, which 
might be different in a few days. 
  This is the result of a flash poll that was carried out by 
the OGM on Wednesday evening (500 telephone contacts that are 
representative of the whole of Austria): Extrapolating from 
these results, 42 percent of the population would vote for 
Austria's entry into the EU in the June referendum, 25 percent 
against, and 32 percent undecided. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

