<F P=100> SPAIN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Menem Concludes Official Visit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0203200894 Madrid RNE International in Spanish 1400 GMT 2 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0203200894 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid RNE International </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Now that he has concluded his official visit to 
Madrid the Argentine President Carlos Menem this afternoon 
begins a private visit in Santiago de Compostela in northwest 
Spain. Carlos Menem will also visit Catalonia. 
  This morning President Menem attended a breakfast at the 
headquarters of the Spanish Confederation of Business 
Organizations with Spanish employers and presidents of Spanish 
banks and large companies. 
  During the breakfast he urged the Spanish businessmen to 
continue to have confidence in Argentina and invited them to 
invest in his country. 
  Carlos Menem stressed the important political transformation 
of his country during the past few years, in particular 
concerning economic policy, which has enabled Argentina to 
reduce inflation from 22,000 [as heard] percent in 1990 to 7.4 
percent last year. 

</TEXT>

