<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   FYROM Official Seeks Support Against Blockade </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0203174794 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1540 GMT 2 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA0203174794 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Ankara, Mar. 2 (A.A.) -- Macedonian Deputy Prime 
Minister Jovan Andonov is currently in Turkey to seek Turkish 
support after a Greek-imposed blockade. "We sincerely believe 
that Turkey will help us," Andonov said. 
  Veysel Atasoy, energy and natural resources minister, said 
before meeting with Andonov that Turkey was one of the first 
countries to recognize Macedonia's [The Former Yugoslav Republic 
of Macedonia--FYROM] independence. 
  Andonov said Macedonia's northern borders and its southern 
Greek border have been besieged and the north-south route was 
the only way for the procurement of raw materials and for 
exportation. Turkey earlier said the Balkan republic could use 
Turkish ports to circumvent a trade blockade imposed by Greece. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

