<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   UN's Feissel Discusses CBM's With Kliridhis, Denktas </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0103214794 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1700 GMT 1 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0103214794 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] President Glavkos Kliridhis held a meeting this 
afternoon with Gustave Feissel, the UN secretary general's 
alternate special representative in Cyprus, within the framework 
of the proximity talks. In a statement after the meeting, Mr. 
Feissel said that the proximity talks will continue on Monday 
but this time at a more intensive pace. He also noted that in 
the meantime the UN officials and the three experts who arrived 
in Cyprus will prepare ideas to submit to the two sides that 
would facilitate the process and aim at achieving an agreement 
on the confidence-building measures [CBM's]. 
  Government spokesman Ioannis Kasoulidhis said that today's 
meeting has concluded this phase of the proximity talks, during 
which the two sides outlined their positions and views and 
exchanged views. 
  This morning, Mr. Feissel had a meeting with Rauf Denktas. 

</TEXT>

