<F P=101> Germany </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kinkel Welcomes Bosnian Muslim- Croats Agreement </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0203174594 Hamburg DPA in German 1700 GMT 2 Mar 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0203174594 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bonn -- FRG Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel has 
emphatically welcomed the agreement [between the Bosnians and 
Bosnian Croats achieved in Washington]. By its dedicated 
participation, the U.S. Administration has made an essential 
contribution to it, Kinkel said in Bonn. Right down to the 
final stage of the negotiations, there was close coordination 
between Germany and its partners, in particular the United 
States. U.S. Secretary of State Warren Christopher expressly 
thanked the Federal Government on the telephone. 
  Kinkel stated: "The momentum for a political and peaceful 
solution to the war in Bosnia-Herzegovina must now be used with 
all one's strength. It cannot and must not be permitted that 
barbarism returns to Europe." Bonn expects the parties to the 
negotiations to settle the remaining open questions with good 
will and with the goal of coming to a lasting agreement. 

</TEXT>

