<H3> <TI>   Kinkel Expects Norway To Reach Positive EU Decision </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0203182594 Hamburg DPA in German 1702 GMT 2 Mar 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0203182594 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Potsdam (DPA) -- Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel 
(Free Democratic Party of Germany) expects the government in 
Oslo to come to [applaud] the positive decision about Norway's 
planned accession to the European Union (EU) by next Monday [7 
March]. After the meeting of the liberal group in the European 
Parliament (LDR) in Potsdam, he said on Wednesday that a 
compromise regarding the problems of fishing quotas is 
foreseeable. Furthermore, Kinkel stressed that Germany will 
advocate more rights for the European Parliament. 
  The LDR group has 45 deputies from 10 countries and is thus 
the third largest group in the European Parliament. It holds a 
meeting in Potsdam from Tuesday to Thursday. 

</TEXT>

