<F P=101> Germany </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ruehe, Thai Counterpart View Security Policy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0203174794 Hamburg DPA in German 1629 GMT 2 Mar 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0203174794 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DPA) -- Defense Minister Volker Ruehe 
(Christian Democratic Union) on Wednesday afternoon [2 March] 
received his counterpart from Thailand, General Vijit Sookmark, 
with military honors in the Defense Ministry. Sookmark has come 
to Germany for a four-day visit. 
  Immediately after the ceremony, the two ministers discussed 
bilateral relations, the development of the international 
security policy situation, and the role of the FRG in the United 
Nations. Ruehe also briefed Sookmark on the experiences of the 
German Blue Helmet soldiers during their mission in Somalia. 
Another subject was the situation in the former Yugoslavia. 
  During his stay in Germany, the Thai defense minister will 
visit the Navy's submarine fleet in Kiel, as well as defense 
technology companies in Kassel and Munich. From Berlin, 
Sookmark will go on to Moscow. 

</TEXT>

