<H3> <TI>   Polls Shows Increasing Support for EU Membership </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0403104894 Vienna KURIER in German 4 Mar 94 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> AU0403104894 </F>
<F P=104>  Vienna KURIER </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "European Spark Ignited: 56 Percent </F>
for Entry; Exclusive Poll for KURIER on Results of EU 
Negotiations in Brussels"] 
  [Text] The grand coalition's euphoria over the conclusion 
of the negotiations in Brussels looks like it has spilled over 
to the population. Twelve hours after the end of negotiations 
in Brussels, 56 percent of interviewees said in a flash poll 
they would vote for Austria's entry into the European Union if 
the referendum were held next Sunday. Only 25 percent would 
oppose it; 59 percent believe they would benefit from the result 
of the negotiations. 

</TEXT>

