<F P=100> AUSTRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Exports to Italy Decreased in 1993 </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0403112294 Vienna KURIER in German 4 Mar 94 p 17 </F>
<F P=103> AU0403112294 </F>
<F P=104>  Vienna KURIER </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Major Decrease in Exports to Italy"] </F>
  [Text] The recession in Italy and the devaluation of the 
lira have resulted in a 14-percent decrease in Austria's exports 
to the neighboring country to the south. Imports only decreased 
by 0.6 percent. In 1993 exports were valued at 36.9 billion 
schillings, compared with imports of 51.2 billion schillings. 
Above all mass products like wood and paper were affected by 
the decrease in exports. 

</TEXT>

