<H3> <TI>   Government Aware of Tripoli Arms Arsenal </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0303184194 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1700 GMT 3 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0303184194 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Bonn (DDP/ADN) -- Chancellery Minister Bernd 
Schmidbauer has confirmed that the German Government has known 
"for some time" about the construction of a weapons arsenal in 
Tahunah, Libya, near the capital, Tripoli. It passed on its 
information to the "competent body of the German Bundestag," 
the minister said in Bonn on Thursday [3 March]. Investigations 
are being conducted into whether German companies have 
"contributed" to the construction of the project, "in awareness 
of the use to be made of it." 
  In close coordination with foreign partners, the German 
Government has pursued "all available information" about the 
construction of the project and "taken all necessary measures." 
According to Schmidbauer, this has "caused considerable 
difficulties for building the structure." [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

