<H3> <TI>   Metal Workers Vote To Strike in Lower Saxony </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0303151794 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1403 GMT 3 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0303151794 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hanover (DDP/ADN) -- An overwhelming majority of 
92.9 percent have voted for a strike in the ballot on industrial 
action in the Lower Saxony engineering industry. This was 
announced to journalists in Hanover this afternoon. According 
to IG Metall, the voter turnout was 97.2 percent. A total of 
41,310 trade union members were entitled to vote, and 40,172 
took part in the ballot. A total of 38,098 voted in favor of a 
strike, and 2,014 against. 

