<F P=100> PORTUGAL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Casualties in Clash Between Cape Verdeans, Police </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0303205994 Lisbon RTP Internacional Television in 
Portuguese 1900 GMT 3 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0303205994 </F>
<F P=104>  Lisbon RTP Internacional Television </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Some 400 Cape Verdeans were involved in clashes 
last night in Prior Velho near Loures [north of Lisbon]. The 
clashes caused the death of one person, and three Republican 
Guards were injured. The incident started at a cafe and went on 
for four hours: 
  [Paula Colaco] Last night was an agitated one in Prior 
Velho. 
One dead and three injured policemen are the results of four 
hours of shooting and stone throwing between the Republican 
Guards and some 400 people of African origin. It all started in 
a cafe, where the residents of the Quinta da Serra shantytown 
usually meet. 
  According to the Republican Guards, the disturbances started 
at about 2000 [2100 GMT], when the cafe owner ordered a 
misbehaving couple to leave. The couple refused to leave the 
premises and the incident developed from there. 
  But some of those present tell a different story: 
  [Begin recording unidentified Cape Verdean witness] The 
couple was doing nothing. We were watching football on TV. The 
boy was sitting and the girl was sitting on his lap. [end 
recording] [passage omitted] 
  For the present, the cafe owner is under arrest, but the 
Quinta da Serra residents are threatening to take justice into 
their own hands. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

