<F P=101> Finland </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ministry Proposes 18 Sep Referendum on EU Entry </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0303170094 Paris AFP in English 1637 GMT 3 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0303170094 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Helsinki, March 3 (AFP) -- The Finnish Ministry of 
Justice has made a preliminary proposal for a referendum on 
September 18 on Finland's entry into the European Union (EU), 
the ministry announced Thursday [3 March]. 
  The government parties have yet to take a final decision on 
the date. 
  Several months are needed to spread information about the EU 
and to allow parliament sufficient time to deal with the 
membership agreement reached March 1, the ministry said. 

</TEXT>

