<H3> <TI>   Kohl, Others Thanked for Role in EU Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0203175294 Stockholm Radio Sweden in Swedish 1545 GMT 2 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0203175294 </F>
<F P=104>  Stockholm Radio Sweden </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Swedish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] German Chancellor Helmut Kohl played a decisive 
role in helping Sweden to reach an agreement with the European 
Union [EU] yesterday, and Prime Minister Carl Bildt thanked Kohl 
for his contributions in a telephone conversation today. 
  [Begin recording] [Bildt] The German contribution was very 
important in the final stages of these negotiations, and we have 
also had reason to thank other people: The Belgian foreign 
minister made important contributions, and we had the 
opportunity to be in contact with the British foreign secretary 
at a decisive stage; so these complement the contributions that 
were naturally made by the Greek chairmanship. I think the 
German political will was of decisive importance. 
  [Unidentified reporter] So without that contribution there 
might not have been any agreement? 
  [Bildt] We cannot know that, but I think that it played a 
decisive role, in that the negotiations were able to continue at 
a critical stage and lead to a conclusion, and it is also 
playing a big role in that negotiations are now continuing with 
Norway and will, I believe, lead to a result. [passage omitted] 
[end recording] 

</TEXT>

