<H3> <TI>   Tension at Greek-Albania Border Over Stranded Trucks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0303200894 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in 
Greek 1800 GMT 3 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0303200894 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Hundreds of trucks and tanker trucks carrying 
fuel remain stranded on both sides of the border checkpoint at 
Kakavyia. Furthermore, tension has risen in Albania following 
the arrest of businessmen from North Ipiros and four Albanian 
customs officers. Our correspondent in Ioannina, Yeoryios 
Kirousis has the following report: 
  [Kirousis] The situation in Kakavyia has become unbearable 
today here as hundreds of trucks have piled up on both sides of 
the Greek-Albania border. The Greek customs checkpoint 
continues to allow passage to only five fuel-carrying trucks per 
day, but problems are now being caused by Albanian customs, 
which processes customs documents at an extremely slow pace. In 
addition, many Greek tanker trucks have been confiscated and are 
being held at the Albanian customs checkpoint. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

