<F P=100> GREECE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Spokesman Calls EU Decision `Positive' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0303221094 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in 
Greek 1600 GMT 3 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0303221094 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Government spokesman Evangelos Venizelos described 
yesterday's decision by the EU [European Union] Commission not 
to take Greece to the European Court for its measures against 
Skopje [The Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia--FYROM] as 
positive. In a statement made today, Venizelos said the EU 
Commission's decision puts the weight on the political aspect of 
the issue, something which the Greek Government has stressed 
continuously. 
  Responding to a question about the revelation in a 
television 
program regarding heroin processing plants in Skopje, Venizelos 
said that the Greek Government will examine the evidence that 
was reported and bring it to the attention of the other Balkan 
countries. He said that it is necessary to clarify the 
situation, and the responsible ministers have already been 
informed and are working on the issue. 

</TEXT>

