<H3> <TI>   Warns East Europe on Subsidies </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0303164894 Paris AFP in English 1627 GMT 3 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0303164894 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Brussels, March 3 (AFP) -- The European Union [EU] 
warned the countries of Central and East Europe on Thursday [3 
March] to put a lid on subsidised agricultural prices and 
production. 
  At a conference in Budapest, EU Agriculture Commissioner 
Rene 
Steichen warned that excessive price subsidies led to expensive 
over-production, as it had in West Europe. A text of his speech 
was made available here. 
  Steichen said the Union was ready to support agricultural 
reform in East Europe, but also intended to protect EU farmers 
against floods of cheap agricultural imports from the region. 

