<F P=104>  London HERMES Database </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Press release from the UK Prime Minister's Office: "Bank of </F>
England Appointments"] 
  [Text] 4 Mar -- The Counsellors of State, acting on behalf 
of The Queen, have approved the appointment, under the Bank of 
England Act 1946, of Sir David James Scott Cooksey and Ms. 
Sheila Valerie Masters as Directors of the Bank for a period of 
four years from 1 March 1994 in place of Sir George Adrian 
Hayhurst Cadbury and Mr. Gavin Harry Laird CBE [Commander of the 
most noble order of the British Empire] whose terms of office 
expired on 28 February 1994. 
  The Counsellors of State have also approved the 
re-appointment of Sir David Gerald Scholey CBE as a Director of 
the Bank, on the expiry of his present term of office, for a 
period of four years from 1 March 1994. 
<H5>  Notes for Editors </H5>
  Sir David Cooksey (53) is Chairman of Advent Ltd and 
Chairman 
of the Audit Commission for Local Government and the National 
Health Service in England and Wales. 
  Ms. Sheila Masters (44) is a Partner with KPMG [Klynveld 
Peat 
Marwick Goerdeler]. 
  Sir David Scholey (58) has been a Director of the Bank of 
England since 1981. He is Chairman of the SG Warburg Group plc 
and holds a number of other directorships. 

