<F P=100> ITALY &amp; VATICAN CITY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fabbri Comments on Sending Troops to Bosnia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0503110194 Rome RAI Due Television Network in Italian 0800 
GMT 5 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0503110194 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Due Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Italian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Italian soldiers could be sent to Bosnia to 
reinforce the UN peacekeeping contingent. France and Great 
Britain have requested this from UN Secretary General 
Butrus-Ghali. 
  Foreign Minister Beniamino Andreatta said that he has not 
yet 
received any official request but that he would not set any 
conditions. Although Defense Minister Fabio Fabbri has not 
denied the possibility, he pointed out that the government would 
have to make a collective decision. 

</TEXT>

