<F P=100> GREECE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Pangalos: Turkey `Imitates' Hitler </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0503171194 Athens ELEVTHEROTIPIA in Greek 5 Mar 94 p 4 </F>
<F P=103> NC0503171194 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens ELEVTHEROTIPIA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Gr. Roumbanis] </F>
  [Excerpt] Greek Alternate Foreign Minister Theodhoros 
Pangalos yesterday described the Ankara regime as "far worse 
than a dictatorship." He also said that Turkey was never a 
state of justice, and in some cases imitates and exceeds 
Hitler's policies. 
  Speaking at the presentation of a book about the Greeks of 
Istanbul by Alexandros Alavanos, Coalition of the Left and 
Progress deputy, the Greek alternate foreign minister launched 
an all-out attack against Turkey for its violation of human 
rights and its expansionist policy, for which Cyprus is now 
paying in the most tragic way. 
  At the beginning, both the Greek alternate foreign minister 
and the author referred to the history of the famous 1964 secret 
decree, with which the Ankara government prohibits the Greeks 
living in Istanbul from transferring their properties and 
confiscates the property. 
  In 1980, another law was added to that decree, prohibiting 
the execution of wills for the Greeks living in Istanbul. Both 
men stressed that even though these decrees are contrary to the 
association agreement between the European Union and Turkey, 
they are still in effect. They said the issue will now be 
brought to the attention of the European Union. 
  Pangalos noted that the 1964 decree was inspired by a 
similar 
decree Hitler issued in 1935 that was used to confiscate 
property belonging to Jews. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

