Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Excerpt] Prosperity Party leader Necmettin Erbakan has 
said that developments following the lifting of the immunity for 
certain deputies are contrary to the laws. 
  Addressing an open air meeting organized by his party in 
Kirikkale, Erbakan said the developments are a result of the 
government's bad administration. He said: 
  [Begin Kirikkale recording] A deputy has the right to appeal 
to the Constitutional Court regarding his immunity. A deputy 
might appeal and the court might revoke the decision. If the 
court endorses the decision, then it is issued in the OFFICIAL 
GAZETTE. Only then can the decision on lifting the immunity be 
implemented. These are the requisites of a state of law. [end 
recording] [passage omitted] 

