<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   EP Asks To Add `Social Clause' to GATT </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR0703135094 Rome ANSAMAIL Database in English 1157 GMT 7 
Mar 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR0703135094 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome ANSAMAIL Database </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "GATT: Social Clause Requested by </F>
European Parliament"] 
  [Text] Strasbourg, 7 Mar (ANSA) -- The European Parliament 
[EP] has requested the inclusion of a "social clause" in the new 
General Agreement on Tariffs and Trade (GATT) to be signed in 
Marrakesh this April, it was learned here today. 
  The clause's objective would be to lay down stipulations 
prohibiting forced labour and the employment of minors to be 
contained in the international regulations that govern world 
trade. 
  "In a world in which commercial exchange takes on a global 
dimension and markets no longer have frontiers, commercial 
activity could prove a forceful means of promoting social 
innovation and improving conditions for the weaker sections of 
society in the poorer countries," the European Parliament 
declared in defence of its request. 

</TEXT>

