<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   North Rhine-Westphalia To Deport Yugoslav Refugees </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0403174694 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1658 GMT 4 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0403174694 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Duesseldorf (DDP/ADN) -- A large number of the 
Serbs, Montenegrins, and Kosovo Albanians living in North 
Rhine-Westphalia are evidently to be deported shortly. The 
North Rhine-Westphalian Interior Ministry in Duesseldorf 
confirmed a report in the NEUE RUHR/RHEIN ZEITUNG paper, 
(Saturday's edition), according to which they will be returned 
by aircraft via the Romanian town of Temesvar and thereafter 
proceed by bus to the Serbian border. 
  Those involved numbered "probably a few thousand" refugees 
whose applications for asylum were rejected. People from rump 
Yugoslavia who were living in Germany illegally or who had 
committed criminal offenses were also likely to be deported, the 
report said. 

</TEXT>

