<F P=100> BENELUX </F>
<F P=101> Belgium </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chile Confirms Purchase of 20 Mirage Planes </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0803120194 Brussels Radio Vlaanderen International in 
English 1000 GMT 8 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0803120194 </F>
<F P=104>  Brussels Radio Vlaanderen International </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Chile is to buy 20 Mirage fighter planes from 
Belgium. This was confirmed by the Chilean defense minister. 
The 20 planes will replace the Chilean British planes which 
date from the fifties. It's not known exactly how much the 
Chileans are paying for the planes, but an amount of three 
billion francs was mentioned earlier. The planes are up for sale 
as a result of the cutbacks in the Belgian Army. The planes 
were previously refurbished. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
